# Constant Fold Nested Function Calls

## Description

Folds nested function calls bottom-up when all leaf arguments are
constants. UPPER(CONCAT('hello', ' world')) first folds CONCAT to
'hello world', then UPPER to 'HELLO WORLD'.

**When to apply**: A function call's arguments are all either
constants or other foldable function calls with constant arguments.

## Implementation

```rust
// Bottom-up folding: inner functions fold first
rw!("constant-fold-nested-unary";
    "(?func (literal ?val))" =>
    "(literal (eval-func ?func ?val))"
    if is_constant_foldable("?func")
),
rw!("constant-fold-nested-binary";
    "(?func (literal ?a) (literal ?b))" =>
    "(literal (eval-func ?func ?a ?b))"
    if is_constant_foldable("?func")
),
```

## Test Cases

```sql
-- Positive: nested string functions
SELECT UPPER(CONCAT('hello', ' world'));
-- Step 1: CONCAT -> 'hello world'
-- Step 2: UPPER -> 'HELLO WORLD'

-- Positive: nested math
SELECT ABS(FLOOR(-3.7));
-- Step 1: FLOOR(-3.7) -> -4
-- Step 2: ABS(-4) -> 4

-- Positive: deep nesting
SELECT LENGTH(UPPER(TRIM('  hello  ')));
-- Step 1: TRIM -> 'hello'
-- Step 2: UPPER -> 'HELLO'
-- Step 3: LENGTH -> 5

-- Negative: column in nested call
SELECT UPPER(CONCAT(name, ' - ', title)) FROM emp;
-- Cannot fold: name and title are columns
```

